{
  "info": {
    "name": "Career Path Analyzer — local DSS (catalog + pipeline)",
    "_postman_id": "c7a9e2b1-career-local",
    "description": "Import once; adjust **Collection variable** `base_url` if your server differs.\n\n**Requirements**\n- Django **`DEBUG=True`** (otherwise **`/api/test/*`** returns **404**).\n- Catalog seeded (`python manage.py seed_catalog`).\n- Server: `python manage.py runserver` from `backend/`.\n\n**Suggested order**\n1. **Catalog → skills list** — sets `skill_id_1` … `skill_id_4` from the DB.\n2. **Catalog → jobs list** — sanity-check titles/salary.\n3. **Debug → similarity preview** — dense cosine skill match only.\n4. **Debug → pipeline preview** — similarity → **`threshold`** → decision matrix (skill match, salary, demand, learning effort) → **AHP** (`pairwise`, 6 rows) → **TOPSIS** → `ranked_jobs` (+ gaps).\n\n**Pipeline body notes**\n- `pairwise` must list **exactly six** unordered criterion pairs (`skill_match`, `salary`, `demand`, `learning_effort`). Same shape as **`POST /api/analyze`** in the spec.\n- `threshold`: default in code is **0.4**; use **`0.0`** in the \"full rank\" request so all fetched jobs survive filtering while you experiment.\n- `learning_effort` = mandatory skills still at weight 0 + framework OR slots where the user has **no** skill in that slot.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {"key": "base_url", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:8000"},
    {"key": "skill_id_1", "value": "1", "description": "Auto-set from GET /api/skills/"},
    {"key": "skill_id_2", "value": "2"},
    {"key": "skill_id_3", "value": "3"},
    {"key": "skill_id_4", "value": "4"}
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Catalog",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "skills list (auto-fills skill_id_1..4)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "try {",
                  "  var j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Is array', function () { pm.expect(Array.isArray(j)).to.be.true; });",
                  "  for (var i = 0; i < Math.min(4, j.length); i++) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('skill_id_' + (i + 1), String(j[i].id));",
                  "  }",
                  "} catch (e) {}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{"key": "Accept", "value": "application/json"}],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/skills/"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "jobs list",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{"key": "Accept", "value": "application/json"}],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/jobs/"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "courses list",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{"key": "Accept", "value": "application/json"}],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/courses/"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
